         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679"><!-- p5l4-r7 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Hd1e108">Rubrica 7</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Hd1e111" type="question-title">Quid mors non sit metuenda</head>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e114">
             <!--title omitted, Rubric 7 continues on from Rubric 6--> 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e121">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e120">CRonica de <!--line bumps up--> nugis philosophurum <!--line bumps back down--> capitulo. 15. scilicet de anaxa<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>gora.</ref> 
             ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e131">Anaxagoras ad an<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>xiantem
             quod in terra extranea more<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>retur
             Undique inquit similis est de<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>scensus 
             ad inferos.</quote> 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e139">
             <!--paragraph omitted-->
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e150">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e152">TUllius tuscula<!--line bumps up-->narum questionum <!--line bumps back down--> libro 1. in finali.</ref> ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e154">Teneamus 
             <lb ed="#O"/>ut nichil <sic>tenseam</sic>
             <lb ed="#O"/>esse malum quod fit anatura datum omnibus.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e162"> 
             <lb ed="#O"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e164">libro. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e164">Qui id quod uitari non potest me<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tuit 
             is uiuere animo quieto nullo 
             <lb ed="#O"/>modo potest. ¶ Qui mortem non ti<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>met 
             <pb ed="#O" n="229-v"/>
             <cb ed="#O" n="a"/>
             <lb ed="#O"/>magnum is presidium sibi ad 
             <lb ed="#O"/>beatam uitam comparat.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e174">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e180">OUidius epistolarum. 10. epistola.</ref> <!--line bumps up--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e178">Occur<!--line bumps back down-->runt 
             animo pereundi mille figure. Mors<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>que 
             minus pene quam mora mor<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tis 
             habet</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e186">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e194">QUin<!--line bumps up-->tilianus declamationum. 3. declamatione.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e190">quisquis honestis operatus 
             <lb ed="#O"/>artibus sciat quis finis que
             <lb ed="#O"/>natura felicitas numquam sibi uide<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>bitur 
             praematura mortem periturus. ¶ lu<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>cis 
             causas ad animum mentemque referen<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tium 
             neminem cotidie uita non 
             <lb ed="#O"/>saciat. ¶ Illa existimemus propter que fa<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tigamus 
             uotis deos propter que bre<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>uem 
             querimur etatem. Nempe sunt 
             <lb ed="#O"/>uanitas cupido luxuria libido
             <lb ed="#O"/>non pudet propter hec ferre debilita<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tes 
             luctus spacia membrorum 
             <lb ed="#O"/>et cum liceat euadere male pati. ¶
             <lb ed="#O"/>Finge tibi uelut ipsam proclama<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>re 
             naturam receptus es in hoc pulce<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>rimum 
             mundi rerumque consortium 
             <lb ed="#O"/>et persuccedentium uices in ordinem 
             <lb ed="#O"/>mortalitatis natus bona nostra 
             <lb ed="#O"/>uidisti admite posteros cede ue<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>nientibus. 
             ¶ Nescis te quanto diu<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tius 
             uixeris tanto magis impatientiam 
             <lb ed="#O"/><sic>perere</sic> quantumlibet prorogentur tempora 
             <lb ed="#O"/>iungantur etates. ¶ Non potest non 
             <lb ed="#O"/>exitu perire miseri qui moritur 
             <lb ed="#O"/>inuitus. ¶ Omnis nos hora per 
             <lb ed="#O"/>tacitos fallentesque cursus appli<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>cat 
             fato et in hac turpissima perpe<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tuitatis 
             cogitatione destricti 
             <lb ed="#O"/>per exigua festinantis eui momenta 
             <cb ed="#O" n="b"/>
             <lb ed="#O"/>premorimur faciamus potius define 
             <lb ed="#O"/>remedium et de necessitate solatium. 
             <lb ed="#O"/>Exeamus sponte consilio pleni se<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>curitatis 
             gratias agentes. Solus 
             <lb ed="#O"/>uixit quo aduoluit qui mori 
             <lb ed="#O"/><sic>mauult.</sic> ¶ Infirme prorsus tene<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>reque 
             mentis est ut numeretis annos.</quote> 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e261">
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e270">SEneca epistolarum ad lucillum. libro 5. 
             <lb ed="#O"/>epistola 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e265">Uita cum expectatione mor<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tis 
             data est ad hanc iter quam ideo 
             <lb ed="#O"/>timere dementis est quia certa expec<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tantur
             dubia metuuntur. ¶ Puto 
             <lb ed="#O"/>fortiorem esse qui in ipsa morte est. 
             <lb ed="#O"/>quam qui contra mortem. Mors enim 
             <lb ed="#O"/>admota est imperitis animum dedit 
             <lb ed="#O"/>non uitandi ineuitabilia.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e282"> 
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e291">libro 7. epistola 
             <lb ed="#O"/>8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e284">Bene mori est libenter mori.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e289">
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e300">
             <lb ed="#O"/>libro 20. et finali. epistola 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e291">Nullum animal ad uitam 
             <lb ed="#O"/>prodit sine motu mortis.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e299"> 
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e313">Idem 
             <lb ed="#O"/>declamationum. libro 3. capitulo 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e301">Crudelius est 
             <lb ed="#O"/>quam mori semper mortem timere.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e307"> 
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e323">Idem de
             <lb ed="#O"/>remediis fortuitorum. capitulo 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e309">Omnium qua horre<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>mus
             exitus spectat ad mortem.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e317"> 
             <lb ed="#O"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e336">2. capitulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e319"> <!--Quote omitted; ref joined with quote of paragraph d1e327--> </quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e327"> 
             <lb ed="#O"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e348"> <!--ref omitted--> </ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e329">Undecumque ad inferos una uia
             <lb ed="#O"/>est. et cetera.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e335"> 
             <!--paragraph omitted-->
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e346">
             <!--paragraph omitted-->
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e356">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e385">Plinius <!--line bumps up--> de naturali hystoria. libro 7. capitulo 54.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e360">Natura nichil hominibus benigni<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tate 
             uite praestitit melius he<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>bescunt
             sensus membra torquentur 
             <lb ed="#O"/>praemoritur uisus auditus incessus 
             <lb ed="#O"/>dentes etiam ad ciborum instrumenta et 
             <lb ed="#O"/>tamen uite hoc tempus adnumeratur.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e372">
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e403">IUuenalis. libro 4. satyra 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e376">Frontem 
             <lb ed="#O"/>postea animum mortis terrore 
             <lb ed="#O"/>carentem.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e382">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e415">MArcialis <!--line bumps up--> cocus libro undique su<!--line bumps back down-->scepto. capitulo 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e386">Mortis pale 
             <pb ed="#O" n="230-r"/>
             <cb ed="#O" n="a"/>
             <lb ed="#O"/>tibi timor uite commoda tollit
             <lb ed="#O"/>Nam moreris uiuens dum metu<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>endo 
             peris.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e394">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e429"><!--no ref--></ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e398">Inter nature ponas si munera 
             <lb ed="#O"/>mortem ponas. Te de morte metus 
             <lb ed="#O"/>solicitare nequit.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e404">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e441">AUctor libelli de <!--line bumps up--> formula honeste uite. <!--line bumps back down--> capitulo 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e408">Magnum
             <lb ed="#O"/>animi bonum est non tremere sed 
             <lb ed="#O"/>constare sibi et finem huius uite intre<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>pidus 
             expectare.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e417">
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e456">CAto. capitulo 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e421">Qui metuit mor<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tem 
             quod uiuit perdit id ipsum. 
             <lb ed="#O"/><!--should be new paragraph--> ¶ capitulo. 3. lnque metum leti nam stul<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tum 
             est tempore in omni. Dum mortem 
             <lb ed="#O"/>metuas amittere gaudia uite.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e429">
             <lb ed="#O"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e470">capitulo. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e433">Fac tibi pro penis mortem 
             <lb ed="#O"/>non esse timendam. Que bona si non 
             <lb ed="#O"/>est finis tamen illa malorum est.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-d1e441">
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Rd1e484">BOetius de consolatione. libro 2. capitulo 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e10679-Qd1e445">con<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tinuus
             timor non sinit es<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>se 
             felicem.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
